 a sometimes heartwarming, sometimes harrowing tour of the media that brings us together and tears us apart.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspects. 0aInformation technologyxSocial aspects. 0aTelevision viewers. 0aTelevisionxSocial aspects. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Electronics / Digital.2bisacsh  aAmerican Crime Story.  aBluey.  aDawson’s Creek.  aDuckTales.  aGhostbuster's.  aHalt and Catch Fire.  aHomeland.  aHouse Hunters.  aLeftover.  aMad Men.  aNintendo Wii.  aScandal.  aStranger Things.  aThe Americans.  aThe Real World.  aThe Sopranos.  aThe Wire.  aTiVo.  aTwin Peaks.  aWall-E.  abooks about screen time.  abooks about television.  acriticism.  acultural history.  aculture.  aessay collection.  aessays.  afilm critic.  afilm criticism books.  afilm criticism.  ahistory of tv shows.  amovies.  aperforming arts.  apop culture.  apopular culture.  aroger ebert.  asocial history.  atelevision criticism.  atelevision history.  atelevision.  atv history.  atv shows.  atv.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131912408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023z9783111318165oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075163540uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479820597.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479820597423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/978147